SETUP

---
Copy the sample configuration to your project directory:

cp ~/workspace/ProguardCache/proguard_android_scala.config.* .
cp ~/workspace/ProguardCache/rakefile_sample.rb rakefile.rb

---
Edit the proguard_android_scala.config file to point to your own code.

---
Run rake with CLASSPATH pointing to the jars for proguard and asm, and a -I option to the directory where you've installed ProguardCache:

(Note that the square brackets are for passing arguments to rake.  They're not the standard notation for optional parameters.]

CLASSPATH=~/workspace/experiments/RubyProject jruby -I ~/workspace/ProguardCache/src/main/jruby -S rake -f src/main/jruby/rakefile_sample.rb proguard[proguard_config/proguard_android_scala.config.unix,proguard_cache/scala-proguard.jar]

---
Source

Complete source is available from https://github.com/banshee/ProguardCache
